						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Preemptive multithreading also lets a single task do something that takes a long time, while doing something else at the same time.  So if you have something like a long pathfinding sequence, you can interrupt it for something else.</div><br />True, I see some applications for that such as chess game AI or whatever, but then it could just be a specialized implementation for one specific CPU-intensive task, rather than general purpose pre-emptive multithreading.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
